data.name: Fort Aguada
data.description: One of the most popular tourist spots in Goa. It is well-preserved fort made by Portugal colonists. You should also see a lighthouse, that is part of the fort.
data.admission: Admission to the fort is free.

data.name: Dudhsagar Falls
data.description: Amazing waterfalls which are extremely impressive, you will always remember the magnificent scenery, you can see here.

attribution.title: Majestic DudhSagar Water Falls in Mansoon
attribution.author: Sharat Chandra

data.name: Benaulim Beach
data.description: This beach is one of the most popular in Goa. It has clean sand and bright water. If you want to, you can take a dolphin cruise here.

data.name: Varca Beach
data.description: Another of amazing sandy beaches in Goa. Both water and sand are clean here so why not go swimming here?

data.name: Anjuna Flea Market
data.description: Every Wednesday a large flea market takes place here. It has amazing atmosphere and it is also great place if you want to buy some souvenirs.

data.name: Baga Beach
data.description: A very busy beach, with lots of shacks, eateries and shopping stalls. No doubt you will never get bored here.

data.name: Palolem Beach
data.description: A great beach that offers not only swimming or sunbathing. There are also excellent opportunities for eating out.

data.name: Mapusa Market
data.description: If you are fascinated by exotic markets, this place is must-see for you. It is crowded and hectic. If you want to get good prices you will have to haggle with sellers.

70x70.author: abcdz2000
70x70.title: Excellent Shopping for Goans at Friday Market Mapusa Goa

320x320.author: abcdz2000
320x320.title: Excellent Shopping for Goans at Friday Market Mapusa Goa

data.name: Chapora Fort
data.description: Amazing ruins of an ancient fort. It is located on a hill so it offers amazing view of Vagator beach.

data.admission: Admission to the fort is free.

data.name: Arvalem Caves and Waterfall
data.description: An ancient cave from 6th century with great carvings inside. Close to the caves there is spectacular waterfall.

data.name: Basilica of Bom Jesus
data.description: This fascinating Baroque basilica dedicated to the infant Jesus is on UNESCO list. It is really amazing and monumental and must-see place of Goa.

attribution.title: Nave of Bom Jesus Basilica, Goa, India
attribution.author: Aruna Radhakrishnan

data.name: Candolim Beach
data.description: A popular beach with magical scenery of River Princess, a ship that is stuck at the shores of the beach since 2000.

attribution.title: A view of Candolim Beach, Goa.
attribution.author: FaizanAhmad21

70x70.author: FaizanAhmad21
70x70.title: A view of Candolim Beach, Goa.

320x320.author: FaizanAhmad21
320x320.title: A view of Candolim Beach, Goa.

data.name: Calangute Beach
data.description: Very popular and busy sandy beach. It is full of various stalls, shacks and restaurants. It is great for swimming, you will enjoy your time here.

data.name: Our Lady of Grace Church
data.description: A church built by Portugal colonists on the place of destroyed Hindu temple. The interior of the church is richly decorated with carvings.

data.name: Vagator Beach
data.description: A small beach, that lies in an amazing bay. There are plenty of restaurants and stalls close to it. If you climb the rocks behind the beach, you will have an amazing view.

data.name: Church of the Holy Spirit
data.description: A charming church built in 1564 by the Jesuits. The interior of the church is spacious and has beautiful decorations.
data.admission: Admission to the church is free.

70x70.author: slim_as_snail
70x70.title: kościół Ducha Świętego przy Largo de Igreja

320x320.author: slim_as_snail
320x320.title: kościół Ducha Świętego przy Largo de Igreja

data.name: Cavelossim Beach
data.description: A fantastic beach with clean white sand. It is usually not very crowded, so you will be able to relax without being disturbed.

data.name: Reis Magos Fort
data.description: Ruins of this fort are accessible, so you can explore it on your own, it also offers amazing view of the bay.

data.name: Arambol Beach
data.description: This popular beach is quite busy, however it is still great place for swimming and sunbathing. You can visit one of the restaurants or shops close to it.

data.name: Mahadeva Temple
data.description: A small unique temple, that is made of stone. It looks spectacular with its beautiful carvings inside.

data.name: Mangueshi Temple
data.description: A spectacular temple that offers unique divine atmosphere. One of the must-see places in Goa.

attribution.title: Sri Mangesh temple at Mangueshi in Ponda Taluka, the most prominent among temples, is situated about 23-km from Panaji. The temple is dedicated to the deity of Lord Shiva. It is one of the most visited temples of Goa.
attribution.author: Mangesh Nadkarni

data.opening_hours: Check out the calendar for events.
data.admission: Foreigners are not allowed inside the temple.

data.name: Betalbatim Beach
data.description: A popular but still relatively peaceful beach. It is a great place, if you want to see dolphins, they often swim close to this beach.

data.name: Lord Rama Fort
data.description: A ruins of an ancient fortress that was renovated by Portugal colonists. Inside the ruins there is well preserved church of Saint Antonio.

attribution.title: View from Cabo de Rama fort in Goa
attribution.author: Shobhitns

70x70.author: Shobhitns
70x70.title: View from Cabo de Rama fort in Goa

320x320.author: Shobhitns
320x320.title: View from Cabo de Rama fort in Goa

data.name: Utorda Beach
data.description: A very popular beach often used for swimming and sunbathing. If you get hungry there are some seafood restaurants close to it.

data.name: Agonda Beach
data.description: An excellent sandy and clean beach, that will offer you great place for swimming or sunbathing. If you get hungry there are some restaurants nearby the beach.

data.name: Goa State Museum
data.description: This museum is focused on history of Goa. It houses wide collection of artifacts such as sculptures, carvings, paintings or coins.

data.name: Velsao Beach
data.description: A clean sandy beach that provides perfect place for all summer pleasures. It is not overcrowded so you will be able to find your own place for relaxing.

data.name: Butterfly Beach
data.description: An amazing beach, that is usually quite peaceful because it is accessible only from sea. So you can spend here delightful day.

data.name: Cansaulim Beach
data.description: This beach is famous for its clean golden sand. It is not so busy so if you want to relax this is the spot you are looking for.

data.name: Butterfly Conservatory of Goa
data.description: A fascinating butterflies conservatory that spreads on over 4000 sq meters. You will be able to see the most magnificent butterflies and caterpillars here.

data.name: Mollem National Park
data.description: A protected area, that will impress all of those who like wildlife nature. In this park you can meet lot of animals including tigers.

attribution.title: Mollem National Park, Tambdi Surla Temple
attribution.author: Marcus334

source.name: Wikimedia Commons
source.external_id: File:Mollem National Park, Tambdi Surla Temple.jpg

data.original_name: Bhagwan Mahaveer Sanctuary and Mollem National Park
data.opening_hours: The ideal time for birdwatching is from 6:30 a.m. to 10 a.m. and from 4 p.m. to 7 p.m.
data.admission: All visitors to the park must obtain entry permit.

data.name: Tropical Spice Plantation
data.description: A spice plantation, where you can see the traditional way of growing all the kinds of Indian spices you use in your kitchen.

data.name: Nine Bar
data.description: This bar and music club is typical for their electronic, trance and techno music. If you want to meet young people and enjoy party, this is the right place.

data.name: Braganza Mansion
data.description: A mansion of Luís de Menezes Braganza, very important person in history of Goa. It shows how wealthy landowners lived in the past.

70x70.author: magalhaes
70x70.title: India, Goa, Chandor, Casa Menezes Bragança

320x320.author: magalhaes
320x320.title: India, Goa, Chandor, Casa Menezes Bragança

data.name: Shri Naguesh Temple
data.description: A Hindu temple dedicated to the lord Shiva. It is one of the hidden gems in Goa decorated with striking wood carvings.
data.admission: Foreigners are not allowed inside the temple.

data.name: Mahalaxmi Temple
data.description: A small temple dedicated to the Goddess of the Wealth. It is usually peaceful, so you can admire its architecture without being interrupted.

70x70.author: Vikas Rai
70x70.title: Ganesh Temple in Malaxmi Temple Complex Goa

320x320.author: Vikas Rai
320x320.title: Ganesh Temple in Malaxmi Temple Complex Goa

data.name: Do Deão Palace
data.description: A beautiful mansion built by Portuguese nobleman, it is very valuable mixture of Portuguese and Hindu architecture.

data.name: Our Lady of the Immaculate Conception Church
data.description: One of the oldest churches in India representing typical colonial architecture. It was built in 1619 over a smaller chapel that were standing here since 1540.

attribution.title: Church of Immaculate Conception as seen from the street in Panjim, Goa
attribution.author: AaronC's Photos

data.name: Municipal Market
data.description: A market where you can buy fresh vegetables, fruit or flowers for fair price. The place has great atmosphere.

data.name: Casino Goa
data.description: A casino located on a luxury yacht. If you want to gamble, it is one of few places in India, where it is legal.

data.name: Chapora Beach
data.description: A sandy beach that lies close to the Chapora fort. You can swim here but there are strong undercurrents so be careful.

data.name: Ashvem Beach
data.description: A sandy beach popular mainly by backpackers and young people.  The beach is topless and lot of parties take place here.

data.name: Sé Cathedral of Santa Catarina
data.description: The largest church in Old Goa, as churches here usually are. It is a unique mixture of the European and the Hindu styles.

data.name: Bondla Wildlife Sanctuary
data.description: A natural preserve, where you can meet wild animals such as Sambar Deer or Indian Bison. There is also sanctuary for injured leopards.

data.name: Church of St Augustine Ruins
data.description: A church constructed in 1602 but abandoned in 1835. The ruins however have amazing atmosphere, it is recommended to visit them during your trip in Goa.

70x70.author: magalhaes
70x70.title: Velha Goa - Igreja de St. Agostinho

320x320.author: magalhaes
320x320.title: Velha Goa - Igreja de St. Agostinho

data.name: Majorda Beach
data.description: Another beautiful beach, that is usually quite busy. It is great for relaxing, your summer vacation here will be delightful.

data.name: Viceroy's Arch
data.description: A remain of Portugal rule in Goa. This gate is very beautiful, decorated with sculptures. It was built by Portugal viceroy, a grandson of famous explorer Vasco da Gama.

data.name: Salim Ali Bird Sanctuary
data.description: A unique nature conservatory, that is a perfect spot for true nature lovers. You can admire plenty of species of birds as well as plants here.

attribution.title: India Goa Chapora River Colony of Birds

source.name: Wikimedia Commons
source.external_id: File:India Goa Chapora River Colony of Birds.jpg

data.name: Chapel of St Catherine
data.description: A medieval chapel dedicated to the St. Catherine. It commemorates the conquest of the city by Portuguese on day of St.Catherine.

data.name: Church of St Anne
data.description: The Baroque catholic church that was declared as a national monument. It is unique church with beautiful interior decorations.

data.name: Ramnathi Temple
data.description: A exquisite temple dedicated to the Shri Ramanath Deity. The whole complex of temple is beautiful and worth-seeing.

attribution.title: The Hindu Temple of Ramnathi in Bandivade, Goa, India.
attribution.author: Drshenoy

70x70.author: Drshenoy
70x70.title: The Hindu Temple of Ramnathi in Bandivade, Goa, India.

320x320.author: Drshenoy
320x320.title: The Hindu Temple of Ramnathi in Bandivade, Goa, India.

data.name: Sinquerim Beach
data.description: Enjoy sunbathing on one of the best beaches in the region. If you like water-skiing, fishing or scuba diving - this place will be paradise!

data.name: Convent & Church of St Francis of Assisi
data.description: One of the Roman Catholic churches in Old Goa center. The interior of the church is decorated with amazing painting depicting the life of St. Francis.

attribution.title: Church of St. Francis of Assisi located in Old Goa
attribution.author: Aaron C

source.name: Wikimedia Commons
source.external_id: File:Church of St. Francis of Assisi.jpg

320x320.title: Church of St. Francis of Assisi located in Old Goa

data.name: Church and Convent of St Monica
data.description: The convent was royal monastery in the past. Nowadays it is one of the buildings that are creating the heart of old Goa.
data.original_name: Church and Convent of St Monica

data.name: Public Observatory Panaji
data.description: If you want to watch the sky in the evening and in the night, this public observatory gives you this unique opportunity.

data.name: Ancestral Goa
data.description: A unique museum, that provides unusual expositions focused on rural life as it looks like hundreds years ago.

data.name: Viva Panjim Restaurant
data.description: An atmospheric restaurant very suitable for budget travelers. They offer traditional Goan dishes, so if you want to try this cuisine you should visit this restaurant.

data.name: Mandrem Beach
data.description: A peaceful beach with gorgeous white sand, there are lots of restaurants with delicious food, for those who get hungry.

data.name: Patriarchal Seminary of Rachol
data.description: This Portuguese seminary offers great walk through Christian history. This place is very important for Indian Christians.

data.name: Fatorda Stadium
data.description: A sport stadium that is often venue of important football and cricket matches. It is great experience to see one of the matches here.

data.name: Pillar Museum
data.description: A museum that is focused on an  ancient history of Goa. You will find here many unique artifacts such as sculptures or pottery.

data.name: Safa Masjid Mosque
data.description: This Islamic shrine is remarkable for its architecture and for massive water tank, that lies nearby. Its interior looks gorgeous.

data.name: Mayem Lake
data.description: This small lake is great if you want to have a boat trip. It is also wonderful place for those who like watching birds.

data.name: Sahakari Spice Farm
data.description: Make a stop at the restaurant belonging to the spice farm and taste some of their specialties. You can also buy spices as souvenirs or gifts.

data.name: Chapel of St Sebastian
data.description: This popular chapel has typical white facade and looks like typical colonial building. Visit it to enjoy the colonial atmosphere.

data.name: Goa Government House
data.description: An official residence of Governor General during Portuguese regime, nowadays it is seat of Indian Governor of Goa.

data.name: Museum of Christian Art
data.description: A museum full of valuable paintings and sculptures. The  collections here are focused on artifacts connected with Christianity.

data.name: Secretariat Building
data.description: This charming colonial building was the palace of Muslim ruler Adil Shah, later it was seat of viceroy. Nowadays there are offices inside, but it is still worth a look.

70x70.author: Brian Pinheiro
70x70.title: Adil Shah's palace panaji Goa. The old Goa Government Secretariat.

320x320.author: Brian Pinheiro
320x320.title: Adil Shah's palace panaji Goa. The old Goa Government Secretariat.

data.name: Church of St Cajetan
data.description: A monumental church with typical white facade. Its interior is really impressing and its wooden carved altar looks amazing.

data.name: Hospedaria Venite Resturant
data.description: A very popular restaurant that is a great lunch spot. It has amazing atmosphere and dishes here are also great.

data.name: St. Thomas Church
data.description: A typical colonial church with white facade. It represents valuable mixture of Portugal and Hindu architectonic styles.
data.opening_hours:
Weekday masses: 7 a.m. and 8 a.m. 
Sat: 5:30 p.m. 
Sun: 6:30 a.m. - Konkani Mass, 7:30 a.m. - Konkani Mass, 8:30 a.m. - Children Mass, 5:30 p.m. - Konkani Mass, 9:45 p.m. - English Mass.
data.admission: Tourists who want to visit the church in different times than in which the masses take place must obtain permission from the priest.

data.name: Vainguinim Beach
data.description: A popular beach with opportunity of playing beach volleyball. If you like this sport, it is perfect place for you.

data.name: Archaeological Museum Goa
data.description: This history museum offers great collection of archaeological artifacts of Hindu culture as well as some newer ones.

data.name: Professed House
data.description: A two floor building covered with lime plaster right next to the the Basilica of Bom Jesus. It was seat of Jesuit missionaries during colonial period.

data.name: Rajbag Beach
data.description: People on this beach are usually guests of close large resorts, it is suitable for walks, sunset watching, swimming and sunbathing.

data.name: Casa Araujo Alvares Mansion
data.description: This beautiful colonial mansion was transformed into small museum. You will have the opportunity to see how life of its inhabitants looked like in the past.

data.name: Kristu Kala Mandir Art Gallery
data.description: A gallery that is located in the former archbishop's house. Its collections are focused on modern Christian art artifacts.

data.name: National Cinema
data.description: If you want to enjoy some Indian movies, you may visit this movie theater, it usually plays typical Bollywood movies full of romance.

data.name: Sher-E-Punjab Restaurant
data.description: If you want to have some delicious Indian food, this restaurant with outside terrace may be the right place for you.

data.name: Milsim Goa
data.description: A paintball ground, where you can test your skills and strategy. It is great fun to simulate military scenarios.

data.name: Naval Aviation Museum
data.description: This museum is focused on history of naval aviation of Indian army. You can see lot of planes as well as expositions about important battles.

data.name: Terekhol Fort
data.description: A well preserved fort, that represents unique architecture style. The fort played important role in the Goan fight for freedom in 1825.
